    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-06T20:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 6, 1934—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. Embassy’s despatch No. 444, January 19. Department understands payment of
                    partial service on Greek foreign debt as agreed upon last November continues to
                    be delayed owing to claims of French bondholders association relative to gold
                    clause and other matters. Please telegraph present status and whether British
                    Government has taken or contemplates taking any action to expedite payment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
